REALM
  Define named rectangular sector areas for use in commands.

SYNTAX
  realm [<realm#>] [<x1:x2,y1:y2>]
  real  [<realm#>] [<x1:x2,y1:y2>]

DESCRIPTION
  Realms are numbered rectangular shortcuts (0-49) that let you
  refer to areas of the map by number instead of typing coordinates
  every time.

  realm 0 is always equivalent to all sectors (*).
  Realms 1-49 can be defined to any rectangle you choose.

  With no argument, shows all defined realms.
  With just a number, shows that realm's coordinates.
  With a number and coordinates, defines the realm.

  Once defined, use #N in any sector-spec command to refer to
  realm N.  You can combine a realm with a ?condition by appending
  it with no space: #1?des=m

SECTOR CONDITIONS
  A ?condition can be appended directly to any sector spec (no space).
  This filters sectors matched by the spec:

    ?des=X    only sectors with designation letter X
              e.g. ?des=m  (iron mines), ?des=a  (agribusiness),
                   ?des=h  (harbors),    ?des=f  (food factories)

  See 'info syntax' for the full list of designation letters.

EXAMPLE
  realm 1 -5:5,-5:5         define realm 1 as area near capital
  realm 2 0:10,0:10         define realm 2 as eastern island
  realm                     list all realm definitions
  census #1                 census of all sectors in realm 1
  census #1?des=m           census of iron mines in realm 1
  threshold food #2 50      keep 50 food in every sector of realm 2
  threshold iron #1?des=m 100   keep 100 iron in realm 1 iron mines
  deliver f #2?des=a 200 $  all agri in realm 2 deliver food to dist
  distribute #2 4,6         point all realm 2 sectors to warehouse

